The paper deals with the analysis of reinforcement learning algorithms, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper also specifically focuses on stochastic approximation algorithms, which are commonly used in reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves some mathematical analysis, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
